<subSubSection id="58129108F9E908EDB39C2D930FDAC10B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="65D636AA17126DE2F2D4405569118CC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EDD9460A3E862843348D725AA7FAD2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Name derived from micro- and the genus name 
<taxonomicName id="36052008AE38C0023AAD38BE60E80366" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96190D5B0E17C6238F6A191D7C15FA44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC7DDD08F0CDDFB795E145AC44BC863F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="7A258465B3E9E1B91755453F47B90213" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56AF3DDC715B2DEA697D2F369EC31165" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="2C32F75D2FA04AD3FBA114FDA96CC3DE" authority="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang, 2021" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Micromelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Micromelanconis kaihuiae" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kaihuiae">
<emphasis id="F86B7B7DFBCD5B87C018A78C28E87575" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Micromelanconis kaihuiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C.M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AAD2369CAD92BC9D8EC018920E056547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="6E1999AD1F3894E382140F62726FF389" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1AD57E5A3BB150F1A43C711686D621EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="B1E28D8F22B1874A600A158F11DBA499" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="0BA95CDCFFD1CB7C6E182524A54B36F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sexual morph</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
not observed. 
<emphasis id="47AD3ADDB7A442875A1CF568C1B6AB9E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: Conidiomata acervular, conspicuous, immersed in host bark to erumpent, covered by brown to blackish exuding conidial masses at maturity. Central column beneath the disc more or less conical. Conidiophores unbranched, aseptate, cylindrical, pale brown, smooth-walled. Conidiogenous cells annellidic, occasionally with distinct annellations and collarettes. Conidia hyaline when immature, becoming pale brown, ellipsoid, multiguttulate, aseptate, with hyaline sheath. Conidiomata formed on PDA after three weeks, randomly distributed, and black. Conidiophores unbranched, septate, cylindrical, pale brown, smooth-walled. Conidiogenous cells annellidic. Conidia pale brown, long dumbbell-shaped, narrow at the middle and wide at both ends, multiguttulate, aseptate, with hyaline sheath.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B900D19330D6C47E74AD09C793989C2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FD6A40C6D41113932498FD6B7C751BD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2478BCBB178B5E17C87F2D4ABB749E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="D9045B69BC508FD3541F7BEC9007612E" authority="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang, 2021" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Micromelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Micromelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C7F6165841F91D57C11D88B822BAC53F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Micromelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the third genus after 
<taxonomicName id="07755D5AFEFC8456AE48018F0927B4B6" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Neopseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neopseudomelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12A3A5A31E24B58257BA18A4C2E0BF11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neopseudomelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="995E6D3B9144B04CF64E5C004404E75E" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; X.L.Fan" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Pseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pseudomelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A714099D049F57AD206B43B9EEA490A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudomelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName id="2B7052DA9DAABFB944C21F160A01CE8E" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; X.L.Fan" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Pseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Pseudomelanconidaceae</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C7CAB6D5AF23E641EB69A3D63D2F007" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogram of Diaporthales from a maximum likelihood analysis based on combined ITS, LSU, tef 1 a and rpb 2. Values above the branches indicate maximum likelihood bootstrap (left, ML BP ≥ 50 %) and Bayesian probabilities (right, BI PP ≥ 0.90). The tree is rooted with Nakataea oryzae (CBS 243.76) and Pyricularia grisea (Ina 168). New species proposed in the current study is in blue and the ex-type strains are marked with *." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.79.65221.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/532141" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D482EB7F94919A0C86FE52FFDA86E406" authority="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang, 2021" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Micromelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Micromelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61E39598E8C1E576A840F0E13D5208EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Micromelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is united in this family based on the 
<taxonomicName id="8570476F77D8881E6D04408AADBDDC87" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9E85A7053185F18EBDB21CF3D4649DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like conidiomata, and pale brown conidia with conspicuous hyaline sheath. 
<taxonomicName id="52F8A832B5C0F3C85EC5404AE11AA8C3" authority="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang, 2021" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Micromelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Micromelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FACE508C2D0811C32FD3CC081CDC31C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Micromelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces two types of conidia from natural branches and manual media respectively, which differs from 
<taxonomicName id="50D2910B5A27E63B09FB2490A1E6EE1F" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Neopseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neopseudomelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C97BA8D3F58941B1A174A6BF4AE28D92" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neopseudomelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="21434099682D98FB9C1F31E83AE8A526" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; X.L.Fan" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Pseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pseudomelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="19D752898AEB66C1D45DB2E2B8908AF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudomelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="826DDB634060F583F156EAB1DB28ED34" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="119 - 134" refId="B13" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JDP, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2018a. Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts. Persoonia 40: 119 - 134, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" title="Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" volume="40" year="2018 a">Fan et al. 2018a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F7C125B7112986C70A1837C1304B1A23" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" author="Jiang, N" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1268 - 1289" refId="B23" refString="Jiang, N, Li, J, Piao, CG, Guo, MW, Tian, CM, 2018a. Identification and characterization of chestnut branch-inhabiting melanocratic fungi in China. Mycosphere 9: 1268 - 1289, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" title="Identification and characterization of chestnut branch-inhabiting melanocratic fungi in China." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" volume="9" year="2018 a">Jiang et al. 2018a</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="E716F619200F900AE6E14B35C6C2DD09" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudomelanconidaceae" genus="Neopseudomelanconis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Neopseudomelanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7669A663EE470F5959E55E5DE6DF9AF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neopseudomelanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its septate conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="134B262FE7F70D9354D3E3D824104455" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" author="Jiang, N" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1268 - 1289" refId="B23" refString="Jiang, N, Li, J, Piao, CG, Guo, MW, Tian, CM, 2018a. Identification and characterization of chestnut branch-inhabiting melanocratic fungi in China. Mycosphere 9: 1268 - 1289, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" title="Identification and characterization of chestnut branch-inhabiting melanocratic fungi in China." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/9/6/14" volume="9" year="2018 a">Jiang et al. 2018a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
